                  <hi rend="largeCaps">JOSHUA BRADLEY</hi>, <hi rend="italic">shopman to Charles Johns, of Drury-lane.</hi> On the morn<lb></lb>ing of the 20th of Nov., about half-past eight, I had some scales in our shop</p>
               <p>—I missed them about nine o'clock—these are them—(<hi rend="italic">produced.</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
